definition.value: A polphosphazene macromolecule composed of repeating dichlorophosphazene (-PCl2=N-) units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating propylamine units.
A macromolecule composed of repeating selenophenyl units connected at the 2- and 5-positions.

One of a class of bacterial natural products characterized by either a nine- or ten-membered ring containing a conjugated system of two carbon-carbon triple bonds separated by a carbon-carbon double bond (i.e. a 3-ene-1,5-diyne system).
An organic sodium salt which is a macromolecule composed of repeating sodium acrylate units.
Macromolecules composed of repeating substituted or unsubstituted ethylbenzene units.

Members of a class of potent antitumour enediyne antibiotics produced by cultures of Actinomadura verrucosospora and Micromonospora echinospora. They contain a bicyclo[7.3.1]tridecane system which combines a methyl trisulfide and double and triple bonds in a 3-ene-1,5-diyne relationship.
Any organic entity containing a conjugated system of two carbon-carbon triple bonds separated by a carbon-carbon double bond (i.e. a 3-ene-1,5-diyne system).

A naturally occurring antibiotic and antitumor agent isolated from Actinomadura verrucosopora. Its chemical structure consists of a core bicyclo[7.3.1]tridecadiynene moiety containing a 1,5-diyn-3-ene as part of a ten-membered ring, a alpha,beta-unsaturated ketone with a bridgehead double bond and an attached allylic trisulfide. This ring system is attached at one end by a trisaccharide moiety and at the opposite end by a 2-deoxy-L-fucose-anthranilate  moiety. The trisaccharide consists of a hydroxyamino sugar which is connected to a isopropylamino sugar through a glycosidic linkage and a thiomethyl sugar through an NH-O linkage.
An ester of glyoxylic acid.
The ethyl ester of glyoxylic acid.
A polymer composed of repeating ethyl benzene groups.
A polymer composed of repeating 4-ethylbenzenesulfonate groups.
A polymer composed of repeating 4-ethylbenzenesulfonic acid units.

A polymer composed of repeating sodium 4-ethylbenzenesulfonate units.

A poly(sulfone) macromolecule composed of units connected by alternating sulfonyl (-SO2-) and ether (-O-) linkages.
A poly(sulfone) macromolecule composed of units connected by alternating sulfonyl (-SO2-) and thioether (-S-) linkages.

A macromolecule composed of repeating N(Ph)3 units.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-donepezil. A centrally acting reversible acetylcholinesterase inhibitor, its main therapeutic use is in the treatment of Alzheimer's disease where it is used to increase cortical acetylcholine.
A 2-[(1-benzylpiperidin-4-yl)methyl]-5,6-dimethoxyindan-1-one that has S configuration.
A halophenol in which the halogen atom is bonded to the carbon atom adjacent to the C-OH group.
A 2-[(1-benzylpiperidin-4-yl)methyl]-5,6-dimethoxyindan-1-one that has R configuration.
A heteroatom-bridged calix(hetero)arene.
An acene composed of heteroatom-substituted aromatic groups.

The amino acid zwitterion formed from 3,3',5-triiodo-L-thyronine by tranfer of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group. It is the major species at pH 7.3.

A copolymer macromolecule composed of homopolymeric blocks of 1->4-linked homopolymeric blocks of 1->4-linked sodium beta-D-mannuronate and sodium alpha-L-guluronate residues, covalently linked together in different sequences or blocks. The sodium salt of alginic acid.
